Class MVHashtable<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<K,java.util.HashSet<V>>
        • simple.util.MVHashtable<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - Type of the key.
    V - Type of the stored values.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<K,java.util.HashSet<V>>

    public final class MVHashtable<K,V>
extends java.util.HashMap<K,java.util.HashSet<V>>
    Allows multiple values to be stored for each key. Identical values can be stored for a key if, and only if, the hash is different.
    Created: Nov 3, 2010
    Author:
    Kenneth Pierce
